  <feedback condition="$noFactoring and $ans1.justSubmitted">
  <p>To factor the quadratic expression <m>($expr)</m>, means to split into two factors, if possible. Generally, this means to separate it into two binomial terms, or a monomial term and a binomial term. Here are two simple examples:</p>
<ul>
  <li><m>x^2 + 4x - 5 = (x - 1)(x + 5)</m></li>
  <li><m>2x^2 + 4x = 2x(x + 2)</m></li>
</ul>
  
<p><em>How to check</em>: It is ok to use a bit of trial and error when factoring. Choose a possible factoring, and then FOIL it out to see if it matches your original, expanded quadratic expression.</p>
